    "description": "Minecart Madness is a 2D arcade infinite-runner in the style of early platforming games. Take on the role of an ape in a minecart and ride the rails as far as you can while dodging inbound minecarts and leaping over gaps in the track.<br><br>The game features a variety of game modes, each introducing new challenges and gameplay opportunities:<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Classic - standard, balanced gameplay<br></li><li> Superflat - like classic, but all track segments generate at the same vertical height<br></li><li> Low gravity - enables longer air time at the expense of jump accuracy<br></li><li> Too much brake - near-limitless braking ability<br></li><li> Ultra mega - enemy carts spawn more frequently and move faster<br></li><li> Late start - start with more points and gain an initial speed-boost<br></li><li> Crocodile craze - holes don't spawn, and enemies spawn more frequently<br></li><li> No holes barred - enemies don't spawn, and holes spawn more frequently</li></ul><br>All game modes can also be played with two players on the same system in split-screen multiplayer.<br><br>Minecart Madness supports keyboard and controller input modes for one or two players. All inputs are customizable.",
